                        <bindingDesc>
                          <binding contemporary="true" xml:id="binding">
                            <decoNote xml:id="b1">
                              Ethiopic bookbinding with plain wooden boards and a colorful textile chemise, preserved in its slip case.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="textile"/>
                        </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Boards">
                              Both boards are carved from a yellow wood.</decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Cover">
                              Chemise in pink cloth with a pattern of white flowers. A long stripe of textile is sewn to the tailcap and it extends in order to cover the three edges of the codex.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b6" type="SewingStations">4</decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b7">
                              The sewing is a chain-stitch on four sewing stations (two pairs). The sewing is damaged and repaired so it's not possible to individuate the sewing pattern.
                              The original sewing thread seemes to be of <term key="vegetalThread" ana="#vegetalThread">vegetal origin</term> and waxed.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b9" type="Spine">
                              Small holes are present close to the head and tail of the quires, prabably remains of the tackets.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b11" type="EndLeaves">
                              The first and the last quire. The quality of the parchment of the last quire differs from the the other quires.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b12" type="SlipCase">
                              The book is conserved in a leather two-part slip case with a flap on the inner case and a carrying strap.
                              </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b13" type="Other">
                              Bookmarks inserted in the upper text prick of fols. 32, 39, 64, 72, 90, 101.
                            </decoNote>
                          </binding>
